    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Describe your issue\n\nIn several places, we access the exception state as 3 references: (type, value, traceback). Python 3 has long had the traceback referenced by the exception object itself, and CPython 3.11 and 3.12 clean this up to only store the exception object itself and extract type and traceback from it at need.\r\n\r\nOnce we switch to Python-3-only (in Cython 3.1), we should change the code to read, store and restore only the exception object itself, thus saving two pointers, several temp variables, and a lot of pointer chasing and runtime work along the way.",
